# CI / CD Rules — SimplePicture3D

## Runner OS Constraints

- Windows builds must use `runs-on: windows-latest`.
- Linux builds and frontend jobs use `runs-on: ubuntu-latest` with explicit
  GTK3/WebKit library installation steps.
- macOS builds (Phase 3) must use `runs-on: macos-latest`.
- Never assume the runner matches any local dev machine.

## No Local Paths

Workflow files and scripts must never contain:
- `/Users/` paths
- `C:\Users\` paths
- `/home/<specific-username>/` paths

Use `$GITHUB_WORKSPACE`, `$RUNNER_TEMP`, or relative paths from repo root.

## Matrix Strategy

For cross-platform jobs (Phase 3+), use matrix strategy:

```yaml
strategy:
  matrix:
    os: [ubuntu-latest, windows-latest, macos-latest]
runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}
```

## SP3D CI Pattern — Rust Backend

```yaml
- name: Setup Rust
  uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable
  with:
    components: clippy

- name: Build
  run: cargo build --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml

- name: Test
  run: cargo test --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml

- name: Clippy
  run: cargo clippy --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml -- -D warnings

- name: Security audit
  run: cargo audit
```

## SP3D CI Pattern — Frontend (Node/Svelte)

```yaml
- name: Setup Node
  uses: actions/setup-node@v4
  with:
    node-version: "20"
    cache: "npm"

- name: Install
  run: npm ci

- name: Build
  run: npm run build

- name: Test
  run: npm test

- name: Audit
  run: npm audit --audit-level=high
```

## SP3D CI Pattern — Python AI Backend

```yaml
- name: Setup Python
  uses: actions/setup-python@v5
  with:
    python-version: "3.11"

- name: Install Python deps
  run: |
    python -m pip install --upgrade pip
    pip install -r python/requirements.txt

- name: Test (stub mode — no model download)
  run: python -m pytest python/ -v
  env:
    SP3D_USE_STUB: "1"
    PYTHONPATH: python/python
```

## Linux System Dependencies in CI

When running Tauri builds on `ubuntu-latest`, always install system deps first:

```yaml
- name: Install Linux system dependencies
  run: |
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install -y \
      libgtk-3-dev \
      libwebkit2gtk-4.1-dev \
      libappindicator3-dev \
      librsvg2-dev \
      pkg-config \
      libssl-dev
```

## Secrets

- Never hardcode API keys, tokens, or signing credentials in workflow files.
- Use GitHub Actions Secrets (`${{ secrets.KEY_NAME }}`).
- macOS signing credentials (Phase 3) must use a secrets-based approach.

## Caching

- Cache `~/.cargo/registry` and `~/.cargo/git` for Rust jobs.
- Cache `node_modules` via `actions/setup-node` `cache: "npm"`.
- Cache Python venv if pip install is slow; key on `requirements.txt` hash.
